               is a lower triangular matrix), estimators may be obtained equation by equation using classic least squares applied to each structural equation individually. The estimation procedure in the diagonally recursive case is simple, because the system is a chain of equations rather than a simultaneous system.

Path analysis allows us to decompose the total effects of a theoretical model into direct and indirect effects. Direct effects are standardized regression coefficients. Indirect effects represent the part of the theoretical relationship between variables that is contributed by mediating variables. For computation of direct effects of exogenous variables (x) on endogenous variables (y), the direct effect is found in theBmatrix. The indirect effects are calculated using
